33
00:04:33,539 --> 00:04:35,234
This is very serious.

34
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,806
Before it gets worse,

35
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:42,744
you should get a suspension first.

36
00:04:48,855 --> 00:04:51,119
"Malaysia"

37
00:04:59,899 --> 00:05:01,389
"HANG FUNG SHIPPING CO. LTD."

38
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:29,989
Mr. Tse? I've been looking for you.

39
00:05:30,263 --> 00:05:32,857
One of my staff
left something at the hotel.

40
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:35,797
You've got it, right? Please return it.

41
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:41,369
Yes, the photo album.

42
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,517
You must have seen the shipping schedule,

43
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:57,521
and went to check us out
at the Shipping Company.

44
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:04,257
The guy is too greedy.

45
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,161
I don't care where he's from, kill him.

46
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:07,230
Yes!

47
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:22,973
Petrol.

48
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:09,259
Send him on his way.

49
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:36,415
The body is over there.

50
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:52,295
- What have you found?
- A bag and a HK passport.

51
00:07:52,338 --> 00:07:56,468
Inform the HK Police immediately.

52
00:07:59,111 --> 00:08:01,204
"Hong Kong".

53
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:07,015
"Resignation"

54
00:08:15,795 --> 00:08:17,387
"SUPERINTENDENT MR. MCDONALD"

55
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:19,896
Come in.

56
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:34,711
You remember your old partner,
Skinny Tse.

57
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:39,908
He may have been killed in Malaysia.

58
00:08:40,052 --> 00:08:41,747
The body will be back tomorrow.

59
00:08:48,494 --> 00:08:51,395
You were such friends with him.

60
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:56,263
You'd want to do the case anyway, right?

61
00:09:26,032 --> 00:09:27,329
Freeze, Police!

62
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:37,770
Be care!

63
00:09:46,352 --> 00:09:47,341
"Work carefully and safely"

64
00:09:51,324 --> 00:09:52,518
Informer!

65
00:10:08,507 --> 00:10:09,405
All of you stay back.

66
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,100
Don't move, get back to the station.

67
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:16,374
Are you alright?

68
00:10:16,882 --> 00:10:19,783
- My leg.
- Tse, brace up.

69
00:11:23,749 --> 00:11:24,841
John.

70
00:11:27,987 --> 00:11:30,080
Two more weeks to the wedding.

71
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:32,780
Are you regretting it?

72
00:11:38,297 --> 00:11:42,290
The wedding has to be postponed.

73
00:11:43,235 --> 00:11:45,430
Why?

74
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:51,432
Before it gets worse.

75
00:11:51,644 --> 00:11:53,544
You better apply for suspension first.

76
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:57,209
I have my reasons.

77
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,350
I've taken on Tse's case.

78
00:11:59,518 --> 00:12:01,816
It's best if we wait
until the case is over.

79
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:03,115
Let me take you home.

80
00:12:28,714 --> 00:12:29,806
"Malaysia"

81
00:12:35,221 --> 00:12:37,314
Tse looks pretty good all dressed up.

82
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:38,946
Quite smart.

83
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:41,356
Looks as if he could live to 90.

84
00:12:41,527 --> 00:12:44,826
Then pop, he's gone.

85
00:12:45,364 --> 00:12:47,195
Hope it's not him.

86
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,767
The loose ends from the drug case
may have caused his murder.

87
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:50,927
He was followed to Malaysia.

88
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:54,334
Of course not.
His boss was killed in jail.

89
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,739
Tse hid in S.E. Asia cause he wanted out.

90
00:12:58,544 --> 00:13:01,570
My negligence
forced Tse to go into hiding.

91
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:04,810
Sergeant Lan, I'm Waipong Wong.

92
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,645
Call this rookie 1006 Kwok Keung Lun.

93
00:13:06,819 --> 00:13:08,116
Tell him to meet me at the morgue.

94
00:13:08,387 --> 00:13:11,686
I'm Pak, not Lan.

95
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:13,884
Sergeant Lan has gone on leave.

96
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:15,616
I'll call the rookie for you.

97
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:23,128
Got a call.

98
00:13:28,941 --> 00:13:31,034
- You want to squash me to death?
- Sorry!

99
00:13:31,177 --> 00:13:32,667
Back...

100
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,955
Nurse, is it serious?

101
00:13:47,026 --> 00:13:48,823
Over 10 stitches.
Won't be able to sit for a while.

102
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:50,393
A permanent scar too.

103
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:51,552
Please call me if there are any changes.

104
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:53,721
I'm from the Police. My name is...

105
00:13:54,934 --> 00:13:56,231
Kwok Keung Lun!

106
00:13:57,870 --> 00:13:59,167
And you're Ada?

107
00:14:03,475 --> 00:14:04,464
This is my number.

108
00:14:04,543 --> 00:14:05,737
Call me if something happens.

109
00:14:05,811 --> 00:14:07,904
Call me even if nothing happens.

110
00:14:12,585 --> 00:14:14,780
Shit, forgot to call back.

111
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:25,053
Inspector Ong from Malaysia.

112
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:34,168
- Our Inspector Wong.
- Welcome!

113
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,775
Crime Unit, Chief Inspector Waipong Wong.

114
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,104
I'm Chat Fu Ong.

115
00:14:39,311 --> 00:14:40,403
Just call me John.

116
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:41,604
And me, Ong.

117
00:14:41,981 --> 00:14:42,777
Come inside.

118
00:14:46,619 --> 00:14:47,415
Sorry!

119
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,957
Do you know Chief Inspector Wong?

120
00:14:54,093 --> 00:14:54,991
Is he here? He told me to report here.

121
00:14:55,127 --> 00:14:56,924
I'm 1006, Kwok Keung Lun.

122
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,224
Shit!

123
00:15:02,534 --> 00:15:03,626
Let's begin.

124
00:15:03,702 --> 00:15:06,193
- I'm Kam!
- How are you!

125
00:15:06,772 --> 00:15:08,364
Since Malaysia has notified us.

126
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,474
We've contacted Tse's family.

127
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:11,908
He's been missing for 2 weeks.

128
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:17,579
If Tse's case involves both areas,

129
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:18,947
we'll probably have to go to Malaysia.

130
00:15:19,051 --> 00:15:21,349
- Your turn, Ong.
- Good.

131
00:15:22,454 --> 00:15:23,546
Run it!

132
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:29,917
The deceased was 1.7m,

133
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:32,086
estimated weight 45kg.

134
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:33,921
Was burnt with petrol.

135
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,328
Bruises on his bones.

136
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:38,733
But basically the body is in one piece.

137
00:15:38,904 --> 00:15:42,101
X-ray shows his left leg
has been operated on,

138
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:45,342
where a metal joint was put in.

139
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:49,039
It matches completely with your X-rays.

140
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:34,181
We found his bag at the scene of murder.

141
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:36,293
With a photocopy of shipping schedules.

142
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:38,826
Those circled
are ships bounds for Hong Kong.

143
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:41,827
These duplicated photo
were also in the bag.

144
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:45,635
Do you recognize?

145
00:16:52,311 --> 00:16:54,211
You won't get sick over this.

146
00:16:54,446 --> 00:16:56,141
The mousetachio is Kanin Ho.

147
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:58,339
He owns a shipping Company.

148
00:17:06,825 --> 00:17:09,316
He was obviously blackmailed.

149
00:17:10,295 --> 00:17:12,695
As for Tse' murder,

150
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,355
the only clue lies with him.

151
00:17:15,267 --> 00:17:17,064
But investigating rich men is a problem.

152
00:17:17,236 --> 00:17:18,931
See if you have enough clout.

153
00:17:25,778 --> 00:17:26,676
John!

154
00:17:26,779 --> 00:17:29,179
The guy with Ho is from Malaysia.

155
00:17:29,815 --> 00:17:31,214
Do you know him?

156
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:33,214
He is Ching Han,
doing very well in Hong Kong lately.

157
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:35,343
He's something,
got filthy rich just like that.

158
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:38,655
Can't imagine he has a clean record.

159
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:42,223
What are you up to now, Clumsy Lun.

160
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:43,622
Self-made bugging device.

161
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:50,459
Doesn't work. No sound.

162
00:17:50,636 --> 00:17:51,830
Maybe the batteries are flat?

163
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,663
You're using batteries!

164
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:57,407
It's the age of hydro-electricity.

165
00:17:57,509 --> 00:18:00,205
You just have to spit on it and it works.

166
00:18:00,379 --> 00:18:01,869
- Have you tried the ones you piss on.
- Kam.

167
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:05,644
You with him go away!

168
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:07,581
I'm going with the rookie
to check Ho out.

169
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:19,629
We're C.I.D. From Central Crime Unit.

170
00:18:19,965 --> 00:18:22,160
We would like Mr. Ho
to assist in an investigation.

171
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:23,428
What do you mean by this?

172
00:18:23,569 --> 00:18:24,661
Make an appointment with my office.

173
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:25,964
Should I take a gift too?

174
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:27,670
I'm not kidding you.

175
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,172
Talk to my lawyer.

176
00:18:37,483 --> 00:18:39,178
He's stalling.

177
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:53,020
Kam, can you see over there
by the flag poles.

178
00:18:53,165 --> 00:18:54,860
Someone's taking pictures of us.

179
00:18:57,035 --> 00:18:58,434
Shit, must be a talent scout.

180
00:18:59,204 --> 00:19:01,900
- There's another there on the podium.
- Kam, Lun.

181
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:04,104
You fix the one at the flag poles.

182
00:19:50,889 --> 00:19:52,186
They've planned their exit.

183
00:19:53,392 --> 00:19:54,689
I though only cops tailed people.

184
00:19:54,793 --> 00:19:56,385
How come we're being tailed?

185
00:20:24,856 --> 00:20:25,948
Sign here please.

186
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,457
Sorry, it's urgent.

187
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,216
- Thanks!
- Crime Unit!

188
00:20:29,328 --> 00:20:30,818
Is Inspector Wong there?

189
00:20:30,996 --> 00:20:31,985
Hold on.

190
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:34,991
Waipong Wong!

191
00:20:35,434 --> 00:20:37,129
John, it's me, Maggie.

192
00:20:37,936 --> 00:20:39,767
I told you
we stop meeting each other for a while.

193
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:41,099
Don't call again.

194
00:20:42,307 --> 00:20:43,797
John!

195
00:20:55,687 --> 00:20:57,985
We've got the gay kid who's with Ho.

196
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:01,582
His name is Ah Chi.
Lives in Wanchai, comes out rarely.

197
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:04,821
Only wholesale deals, no retail trade.

198
00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:07,657
Been to every gay hangout
and 2 guys know him.

199
00:21:09,901 --> 00:21:11,698
- Bring him in.
- Yes!

200
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:25,110
I'm Inspector Wong from Crime Unit.

201
00:21:25,217 --> 00:21:26,616
We have an appointment
with Mr. Ho at 4 p.m.

202
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:30,115
Do you have a booking?

203
00:21:30,255 --> 00:21:31,847
How can you say there's no appointment!

204
00:21:31,923 --> 00:21:33,322
I came personally yesterday.

205
00:21:33,492 --> 00:21:35,687
Mr. Ho is busy for the rest of the month.

206
00:22:03,922 --> 00:22:04,911
Open up.

207
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,559
So noisy, must be a gay party.

208
00:22:24,276 --> 00:22:25,174
Open up.

209
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:35,650
Shit.

210
00:23:17,996 --> 00:23:19,190
Is John there?

211
00:23:19,331 --> 00:23:20,923
What? Go on.

212
00:23:21,099 --> 00:23:25,798
The circled ship is arriving today
and will leave in 2 days' time.

213
00:23:25,937 --> 00:23:27,336
Do we have time to apply for a permit.

214
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,935
It's too big,
we won't have time to search.

215
00:23:31,042 --> 00:23:32,839
We'll discuss it when I get back.

216
00:23:52,664 --> 00:23:54,256
The guy's still following.

217
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:56,399
I know I've failed.

218
00:23:56,501 --> 00:23:57,900
Tried twice to meet the guy.

219
00:23:58,069 --> 00:23:59,263
I didn't mean you.

220
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:01,929
I meant those guys are tailing us again.

221
00:24:02,073 --> 00:24:02,767
Tailing us?

222
00:24:02,874 --> 00:24:04,068
- If send up here.
- Where?

223
00:24:04,176 --> 00:24:05,268
Let's play hide and seek.

224
00:24:08,413 --> 00:24:09,505
Don't scare them.

225
00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:11,047
You take one end, I'll take the other.

226
00:24:12,017 --> 00:24:12,915
Go!

227
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:14,579
Careful!

228
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:27,325
Freeze, C.I. D!

229
00:24:37,909 --> 00:24:39,103
Gun, he's got a gun.

230
00:24:53,625 --> 00:24:54,523
Move off.

231
00:24:56,495 --> 00:24:57,291
Freeze.

232
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:07,096
You've got guns too. You can shoot too!

233
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:30,889
Hell.

234
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:49,603
You're lucky to be alive.

235
00:25:49,781 --> 00:25:51,976
Are you alright?
Scared the hell out of me.

236
00:26:54,813 --> 00:26:56,303
Well, Sir?

237
00:26:57,449 --> 00:26:58,541
What about the one you were after?

238
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:00,945
- He got away.
- O. K?

239
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:02,416
Fine.

240
00:27:04,656 --> 00:27:06,351
- Fix them up.
- Yes, sir!

241
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:30,411
Shit! Two are gone in a day.

242
00:27:31,016 --> 00:27:32,608
Looks like a really tricky case.

243
00:27:33,885 --> 00:27:35,785
They really want to know
where we're going.

244
00:27:38,456 --> 00:27:39,650
Ho is leaving for Seattle tomorrow.

245
00:27:39,824 --> 00:27:41,121
What can we do if he leaves?

246
00:27:42,794 --> 00:27:44,386
We can't stop him from going.

247
00:27:44,663 --> 00:27:46,460
But I can fix it so that he can't go.

248
00:27:48,033 --> 00:27:49,523
Kam, let's put on a good show tomorrow.

249
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:50,862
We'll have some fun with him.

250
00:27:51,036 --> 00:27:53,129
Good, it won't so boring then.

251
00:28:04,549 --> 00:28:07,746
What we do to Ho tomorrow
is not in the rule book.

252
00:28:08,253 --> 00:28:09,811
Can lose your job anytime.

253
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:11,420
If you don't want to take part.

254
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:14,385
I'll apply for your transfer.

255
00:28:17,996 --> 00:28:19,896
I'm right behind you.

256
00:28:20,065 --> 00:28:21,555
I can't transfer just after I've started.

257
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:23,232
We'll have some fun!

258
00:28:27,472 --> 00:28:30,270
You got my photos
to coerce me into co-operation.

259
00:28:30,675 --> 00:28:32,643
Now there's murder and you hang in on me?

260
00:28:32,777 --> 00:28:34,472
Who did you kill in Malaysia?

261
00:28:34,679 --> 00:28:36,271
Why are the cops after me?

262
00:28:42,020 --> 00:28:44,215
I've got someone tailing the cops.

263
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:45,686
Anything happens, I'll handle it.

264
00:28:46,458 --> 00:28:47,857
The guy was killed in Malaysia,

265
00:28:48,026 --> 00:28:51,018
so that your photos won't get out.

266
00:28:51,930 --> 00:28:55,661
Your other Board Members
will not like it.

267
00:28:56,701 --> 00:28:57,998
